<item>
            <title>[LU-8304] libcfs_debug_dumplog calls potentially sleeping function in wrong state</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8304</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;libcfs_debug_dumplog() sets task state to INTERRUPTIBLE and then calls kthread_run() that might sleep.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s mostly harmless here, but still should be avoided as the kernel prints a nastygram about it when it happens.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess just moving the state setting to after kthread_run call is all that&apos;s needed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
